===Etymology===
Portuguese [[manga]], from Malayalam [[മാങ്ങ]], Tamil ''māṅkāi''.

The word mango is from the Malayalam (the language of [[Kerala]], [[India]]) word മാങ്ങ /mɑːŋːə/. Portuguese explorers tasted mangoes for the first time in Kerala, and borrowed the word into their language, rendering it as 'manga', which was in turn borrowed into English.

===Noun===
'''mango''' (''plural:'' [[mangoes]])

# A [[tropical]] [[Asian]] [[fruit tree]], ''Mangifera indica''.
# The [[fruit]] of the mango tree.
# ''(US regional)'' A [[bell pepper]].

